### What was built

**Storage layer** (`internal/store/`):
- `parse.go` — Markdown parser/renderer that handles `- [ ]`/`- [x]` syntax, preserves non-todo lines
- `store.go` — Store type with atomic writes (temp-file + rename), directory auto-creation, list discovery, and CRUD operations (Add, Complete, Remove, ListTodos)

**CLI commands** (`cmd/`):
- `root.go` — Root command with `--dir` global flag (defaults to `~/.godos/`)
- `add.go` — `godos add <text> [--list name]`
- `list.go` — `godos list [--list name] [--all]`
- `done.go` — `godos done <number> [--list name]`
- `remove.go` — `godos rm <number> [--list name]`

**Smoke test passed** — all commands work end-to-end including edge cases (empty lists, invalid numbers, already-done todos, multiple named lists).

